      "widgets_values": [
        "MULTI-ANGLE PATCH - CALIBRATION PROOF\n\n1. Generate a novel view of the SAME scene ~35deg to the RIGHT of the\n   recovered camera (Qwen-Image-Edit-2511 + Multiple-Angles LoRA, prompt\n   e.g. '<sks> right side view eye-level medium shot'), or hand-make one.\n2. Load it in the 'Patch novel view' node.\n3. Keep AtlasAddPatchView azimuth_deg = 35 (match the angle asked of the\n   LoRA). elevation_deg=0. For a top patch: elevation ~35, azimuth 0.\n4. Queue, then in the Atlas Viewport hit Camera View, then Project.\n   GO/NO-GO: orbit slightly right - the patch should fill the primary's\n   occluded/grazing right side and stay aligned with it in the overlap.\n   If features line up, constructed-orbit == LoRA-angle holds and the\n   3-patch build is safe. (Needs a ComfyUI restart to load the new node,\n   and a browser refresh for the viewport JS.)"
      ]
    }
